genresAdvancedInfo.name: old school hard trance
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Oldschool Deutschrap refers to the early days of German hip hop, characterized by its raw and gritty sound, socially conscious lyrics, and heavy use of sampling. Artists like Fettes Brot, Advanced Chemistry, and Die Fantastischen Vier paved the way for the genre, which has since evolved into a more mainstream sound. Oldschool Deutschrap remains a beloved and influential subculture in Germany, and continues to inspire new generations of artists.
